passages.text: Germany | Internet Delivery Hero

Calling how the equity will respond to the H1 results is difficult. The good Q2 / H1 results, with a solid EBITDA beat and improving growth are a clear positive, so too, the language in the release relating to "Positive momentum in Asia, highlighted by a return to growth in APAC and improved growth dynamics in South Korea" (and we look forward to the 1pm UK results call to explore this latter comment).

On the negative side, consensus sits \(c.7\%\) behind downgraded FY25 Adjusted EBITDA guidance; it's critical to note however that the downgrade is solely driven by FX, something the market should have largely anticipated given the behaviour of the USD YTD.

In our view, this is an equity most sensitive to trends in Korea; local news flow suggests DH's Baemin has had an incredibly active summer on the commercial front, which is consistent with the comments in the release. For this reason, after some pressure at the open, we would expect to see an overall positive response in the equity today.
2Q25 results are good at the headlines. 2Q25 GMV is in- line vs. company- collated cons, 1H25 segment revenues \(+3.7\%\) ahead, 1H25 EBITDA \(+7\%\) ahead.

Group GMV constant FX growth (excl. Hl accounting) accelerated to \(+9.4\%\) (from \(+7.6\%\) \(+8.2\%\) in 1Q25 / 4Q24). On a like- for- like basis (accounting for exits), GMV and segment revenue grew \(+11\%\) and \(+25\%\) respectively in the quarter (vs. \(+9\%\) \(+22\%\) in 1Q25).

DH has upgraded GMV and segment revenue guidance for FY25, but downgraded EBITDA and FCF. Details: constant FX lfl GMV growth now expected at "upper- end" of previous \(8 - 10\%\) range (1H25a of \(c. + 10\%\) FY25 cons on \(c.9\%\) ; constant FX segment revenue growth of \(22 - 24\%\) previously \(17 - 19\%\) (1H25a of \(c. + 25\%\) , FY25 cons on \(c.19.5\%\) ), reflecting "accelerated Q2 growth [underpinned] by stronger growth across several markets and an accelerated roll- out of the delivery network in South Korea"; Adjusted EBITDA of €900- 940m, \(c. - 8\%\) vs previous range of €975- 1,025m \((- 7\%\) vs. cons. €993m, 1H25a of €411m), driven by a \(c.110m\) FX headwind; FCF of \(>120m\) , \(c. - 40\%\) from \(>200m\) previously ( \(c. - 45\%\) vs. cons. €217m), the change is driven by a \(c.80m\) FX headwind.

Delivery HeroDelivery Hero AG is a holding company that engages in the operation of online food ordering portals. It develops an online platform, providing users with information on local restaurants and their delivery services. It offers consumers access to online menu cards, order placement, and payment processing applications. The company was founded by Niklas Östberg, Markus Fuhrmann, Lukasz Gadowski, and Kolja Hebenstreit in May 2011 and is headquartered in Berlin, Germany.
Valuation: DCF- based, supported by multiples. Risks include aggressive competition and gig economy regulation.
